{"key":"post-14313530","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>14313530</id>\n<content>You should never use a rheostat to control an AC appliance.&amp;nbsp; It's a fire hazard will also risk burning up the device.&amp;nbsp; AC circuits are controlled by frequency or chopping off part of the sine wave, but not by limiting current throughout the whole wave.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You don't need to be using an incubator, and you don't need a fogger.&amp;nbsp; Perlite will give you 99% humidity in a terrarium, and a cool mist without a fogger will give you 90% or better in a mini-greenhouse.&amp;nbsp; A fogger runs the risk of saturating the air and/or the substrate, which you don't want.&amp;nbsp; For a substrate to perform properly, it should be losing moisture due to evaporation.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>14313698</next>\n<prev>14313358</prev>\n<first>14313358</first>\n<last>14314140</last>\n<when>1303177827</when>\n<utime>04/19/11 04:50 AM</utime>\n</post>"}